-------------

.. code:: python

    p, r, b = 10, 28, 8.0 / 3
    
    with reaction_rules():
        ~x > x | (-p * x + p * y)
        ~y > y | (-x * z + r * x - y)
        ~z > z | (x * y - b * z)

Tamari attractor
----------------

.. code:: python

    a = 1.013
    b = -0.021
    c = 0.019
    d = 0.96
    e = 0
    f = 0.01
    g = 1
    u = 0.05
    i = 0.05
    
    with reaction_rules():
        ~x > x | ((x - a * y) * cos(z) - b * y * sin(z))
        ~y > y | ((x + c * y) * sin(z) + d * y * cos(z))
        ~z > z | (e + f * z + g * a * atan((1 - u) / (1 - i) * x * y))

Moore-Spiegel attractor
-----------------------

.. code:: python

    T, R = 6, 20
    with reaction_rules():
        ~x > x | y
        ~y > y | z
        ~z > z | (-z - (T - R + R * x * x) * y - T * x)

.. code:: python

    run_simulation(numpy.linspace(0, 100, 5001),
                   y0={'x': 1, 'y': 0, 'z': 0},
                   return_type='nyaplot', opt_args={'x': 'x', 'y': 'y'})
